{{Infobox museum
| name             = Lampeter Museum
| map_type         = Wales Ceredigion
| map_caption      = Old Porter's Lodge, College Street
| coordinates      = {{coord|52.113274|-4.077997|display=inline}}
| established      = 16 May 2014
| location         = [[Lampeter]], [[Ceredigion]], [[Wales]] 
| type             = Local History
| website          = [http://hanesllambed.org.uk Official website]
}}

The '''Lampeter Museum''' was founded by Hanes Llambed, the local history society, in 2014 at the town's university campus.<ref>{{cite web|title=Museum celebrates Lampeter's rich history|url=http://www.uwtsd.ac.uk/news/press-releases/press-releases-2014/museum-celebrates-lampeters-rich-history-.html|website=uwtsd.ac.uk|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref> In Welsh, it is known as Amgueddfa Llambedr Pont Steffan.
The museum covers the cultural and agricultural development of the town as well as the history of the college which was founded in 1822. The first exhibition hosted by the museum was about the town during the first world war.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-mid-wales-27501446|title=New Lampeter museum at campus celebrates town's history|website=BBC News|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref>

