== 2009 Controversy ==
The overall 2009 competition winner, José Luis Rodriguez, was stripped of his award and his £10,000 prize following allegations that his picture of a wolf leaping a gate had been staged, using a captive animal to do so. He was also prohibited from entering the competition for life. It was, however, too late to remove the image from the accompanying book.<ref name="Booth">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2010/jan/20/wolf-wildlife-photographer-award-stripped|title=Wildlife photographer of the year stripped of his award|last=Booth|first=Robert|date=2010-01-20|work=The Guardian|accessdate=24 March 2010}}</ref>
